import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='speed', kde=True)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wind speed?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

    plt.title('What is the relationship between wind speed and wind direction?', wrap=True)

import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.countplot(x='dirCat', data=data)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of categorical wind direction?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the geographical distribution of wind vectors?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
